The BA area covers a good bit of the [[South Somerset]] district, but not all of it - nor, indeed, all of the area of south Somerset, which has to include the new [[Somerset West and Taunton]] district as well. It certainly covers all of the area of east Somerset, however.

It is that bit less cumbersome and that bit more appealing to casual readers, IMO, to simply say that the postcode districts are "within" the post towns, as opposed to them being "subdivisions". In this area, CV8 covers part of the Coventry post town and the entire Kenilworth post town - so it can be said that the Kenilworth post town is a subdivision of CV8, rather than the other way round. See also BR2 (part of Bromley and all of Keston) and PO13 (part of Gosport and all of Lee-on-the-Solent).
No post town or settlement anywhere called "Digiton", AFAIK

It is that bit less cumbersome and that bit more appealing to casual readers, IMO, to simply say that the postcode districts are "within" the post towns, as opposed to them being "subdivisions". In this area, LE67 covers the Coalville, Markfield and Ibstock post towns in their entirety - so it's really the case that these three post towns are subdivisions of LE67, rather than the other way round. See also OX18, CR8, KT8 and RH6 among others.

I'd keep the bit about the parts of local government districts covered by the WD area, for the time being at least - most of the area lies within the M25, and the articles on other areas lying outside the London post town but largely or wholly within the motorway (BR, CR, DA, EN, HA, IG, KT, RM, SM, TW, UB) also point out the parts of local government districts covered by these areas. I have, however, tidied up this bit, and fleshed out the Watford Observer reference too.

IMO, it is that bit less cumbersome and that bit more appealing to casual readers to simply say that the postcode districts are "within" the post towns, as opposed to them being "subdivisions". There are, of course, postcode districts that cover more than one post town (e.g. CR3, CR8, BR2, KT8, RH6, OX18) - in these cases, the post towns are subdivisions of the postcode districts, rather than the other way round.
